cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the optimization of delivery time in a coded caching and transmission scheme. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper studies a fog radio access network and its connectivity. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a scheme to minimize delivery time in a partially-connected network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with the delivery of files from a library to users. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper proposes a centralized coded caching and delivery scheme for a fog radio access network.
